commentTextItems.html: tossed, on leg, Chakabva tries to reverse sweep, gets struck on the pad, ball loops towards keeper

commentPostTextItems.html: And that is it! Zimbabwe have won by 4 runs (D/L method) to go 2-0 up. The hosts looked to be in trouble at 92 for 4 in the 16th over then came captain fantastic.

Moor targeted mainly the spinners cruising to an unbeaten 33 ball 45 , smashing 3 towering sixes in the process. Chakabva anchored the innings with an unbeaten 78 and both contributing 93 runs off 80 balls for the fifth wicket.
PJ Moor is the man of the match for his 45 not out. That will be all for today . See you on Sunday for the third match
